title: Want To Buy:  Ar15
postcontent: Ok guys, we all need to take a step back and try to have some level of self realization. If I build an engine for $30,000 and I decide to sell it on the street, I will not get $30,000 out of it. The exact same applies to the ar15 as well. If I buy a bunch of hot rod, badass parts from 20 different manufacturers and have Joe blow down at the local gun shop slap it all together, I've got an awesome gun that I will probably lose my ass on if I try and sell it. This is the unfortunate reality of the situation. There is nothing wrong with the gun, but most people want a factory weapon. So most of you guys either need to take a loss because you really want it gone, or get enough use out of it to justify the loss.
